# Chapter 7 - AI in Black Hole Detection

This project simulates black hole light curve data and trains a basic neural network classifier to detect black hole events.

## Features

- Synthetic generation of stellar and black hole light curves  
- Binary classification using TensorFlow/Keras  
- Evaluation of prediction accuracy

## Requirements

- Python 3.x  
- numpy, matplotlib  
- tensorflow  
- scikit-learn

## How to Run

Run the notebook in Google Colab. Modify noise and signal parameters to test robustness.

## References

- [NASA AI Projects](https://www.nasa.gov/ai)  
- [TensorFlow for Astronomical Analysis](https://www.tensorflow.org/)
